## Prototype desc

Prototype shows how to manage the lighting of a virtual hotel with a simple dashboard.
Ability to manipulate lights one room or area at the time, multiple rooms at the same time or one floor at the time.
Shows how to set lights to come on and off at a specific time. App has different user levels with diffrerent privliges: Admin,manager,quest.
Prototype shows potential customer how product makes light management easy, flexible and fast.

## Product reqs demonstrated

- 01 Guests must be able to adjust their own and only own their rooms lighting
  - Shows the products advantage from guest point of view and shows guest can access only their room
- 04 Admin level dashboard that allows to control the lights in groups. Example: one floor at a time
  -Shows the main functionality of the product. The ability to control lights of whole hotel in different size segments easily
- 05 Admin level dashboard shows state of all lights
  - Gives customer the overview of the product dashboard. Shows how easy it is to get a picture of the hotels lighting at every given moment
- 06 Lights can be set to come on and off at specific times
  - Customer can see how they can take advantage of timed lighting. A night manager can set lighting ready for next days conference rooms
- 07 Must have password protected access and different levels of users: manager, normal etc
  - Rudimentary implemetation, but demonstrates that we are serious and always thinking about security
